📌 Advanced Financial Analysis Prompts (English)
1. Profitability Deep Dive
“Conduct a profitability analysis by breaking down gross margin, operating margin, and net margin trends over 10 years. Attribute changes to cost structure, pricing strategy, and market conditions.”

“Benchmark profitability ratios against top 3 competitors and industry averages, highlighting competitive advantages or weaknesses.”

2. Capital Structure & Leverage
“Analyze the company’s debt-to-equity ratio, interest coverage, and leverage trends. Assess implications for cost of capital and financial flexibility.”

“Model impact of a 20% increase in debt financing on EPS, ROE, and credit rating.”

3. Liquidity Stress Test
“Evaluate short-term liquidity using current ratio, quick ratio, and cash ratio. Simulate a 30% drop in receivables collection speed and assess solvency risk.”

“Prepare a working capital cycle analysis, identifying bottlenecks in inventory turnover and receivables management.”

4. Growth & Revenue Drivers
“Decompose revenue growth into volume, price, and mix effects. Identify top 3 product lines contributing to growth and assess sustainability.”

“Perform CAGR analysis for revenue, EBITDA, and net income over 5 years. Compare with peer group growth rates.”

5. Cost Efficiency & Productivity
“Conduct a cost structure breakdown (COGS, SG&A, R&D). Identify areas of cost creep and propose efficiency measures.”

“Perform activity-based costing analysis to evaluate profitability of each business unit.”

6. Valuation & Market Multiples
“Perform a DCF valuation with sensitivity analysis on WACC and terminal growth rate. Present valuation range under optimistic and pessimistic assumptions.”

“Compare EV/EBITDA, P/E, and P/B multiples against industry peers. Highlight undervaluation or overvaluation signals.”

7. Risk & Scenario Planning
“Run Monte Carlo simulations on revenue forecasts to estimate probability distribution of outcomes.”

“Stress test portfolio under oil price shock, interest rate hike, and currency depreciation scenarios.”

8. Shareholder Value Creation
“Evaluate shareholder returns using TSR (Total Shareholder Return), dividend yield, and buyback impact.”

“Analyze ROE decomposition using DuPont analysis to identify drivers of shareholder value.”
